Package: seededlda
Type: Package
Title: Seeded-LDA for Topic Modeling
Version: 0.5
Authors@R: c(person("Kohei", "Watanabe", email = "watanabe.kohei@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
             person("Phan", "Xuan-Hieu", email = "pxhieu@gmail.com", role = c("aut")))
Description: This package implements the seeded-LDA model (Lu, Ott, Cardie & Tsou 2010) 
    <https://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?id=2119585> using the quanteda package and the GibbsLDA++ library. 
    Semisupervised LDA model allows users to pre-define topics with keywords to perform theory-driven analysis of textual data
    (Watanabe & Zhou 2020)<https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/full/10.1177/0894439320907027>.
License: GPL-3
URL: https://github.com/koheiw/seededlda
BugReports: https://github.com/koheiw/seededlda/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends:
    R (>= 3.5.0),
    quanteda (> 2.0),
    methods
Imports:
    Matrix
LinkingTo: Rcpp, RcppParallel, RcppArmadillo (>= 0.7.600.1.0), quanteda
Suggests:
    testthat,
    quanteda.textmodels
RoxygenNote: 7.1.1
